poem each focuses a story

00:07:34.030 --> 00:07:37.780
for his first meeting with
Carla Hayden our 14th Librarian

00:07:37.780 --> 00:07:39.080
of Congress.

00:07:39.080 --> 00:07:41.960
But he doesn't just
wheeled a skilled pen,

00:07:41.960 --> 00:07:47.070
Juan Filipe has been one of the
most active Poet Laureates ever.

00:07:47.070 --> 00:07:50.610
In his first term, he
launched the online initiative

00:07:50.610 --> 00:07:54.290
"La Casa de Colores;
The House of Colors."

00:07:54.290 --> 00:07:57.980
It includes the epic crowd
source poem "La Familia"

00:07:57.980 --> 00:08:00.970
which echoed the diverse
voices of America.

00:08:00.970 --> 00:08:06.560
He also produced the
video series "El Jardin;

00:08:06.560 --> 00:08:10.170
The Garden" in which he
walked viewers through some

00:08:10.170 --> 00:08:12.910
of the library's surprising
treasures.

00:08:12.910 --> 00:08:18.550
For his second term, Juan Filipe
focused on connecting with youth.

00:08:18.550 --> 00:08:22.990
He launched "The Technicolor
Adventures of Catalina Neon",

00:08:22.990 --> 00:08:28.240
an online collaboration with
illustrator Juana Medina

00:08:28.240 --> 00:08:30.380 position:56%
which swept second and third graders

00:08:30.380 --> 00:08:34.530
into the wonders of
the creative process.

00:08:34.530 --> 00:08:37.090
He also launched "Wordstreet
Champions

00:08:37.090 --> 00:08:39.010
and Brave Builders of the Dream."

00:08:39.010 --> 00:08:43.050
A yearlong project with
Chicago public libraries

00:08:43.050 --> 00:08:47.670
and the Poetry Foundation, which
excuse me, Chicago public schools,

00:08:47.670 --> 00:08:51.410
Chicago public libraries,
and the Poetry Foundation

00:08:51.410 --> 00:08:55.250
which gave educators new
strategies for teaching poetry.

00:08:55.250 --> 00:08:59.050
